    },
    "body": "I'm running into OOM issues at long sequence lengths with deepseek r1, so exploring options here (see [o3-mini chat](https://chatgpt.com/share/67b7970b-6858-8009-ab03-288cd37fffdf)). First I tried moving the silu+mul to be an inplace operation via a new kernel `torch.ops._C.silu_and_mul_inplace(intermediate_cache1.view(-1, N))`, but it seems easier to reuse memory for cache1 and cache3 since there is absolutely no data dependency there\n\nManual peak measurement shows 15% reduction in memory for fused_moe for 64k prefill\n\nEval:\n```\nvllm (pretrained=deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-Coder-V2-Lite-Instruct,trust_remote_code=True), gen_kwargs: (None), limit: None, num_fewshot: 5, batch_size: auto\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.7642|±  |0.0117|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.7468|±  |0.0120|\n```",
    "created_at": "2025-02-20T18:34:43Z",
